TXL Example Program
-------------------

Name:   
        C++.Grammar
        cp.Txl
        cpcount.Txl

        ANSIC.Grammar
        c.Txl
        ccount.Txl

Description:
        C++.Grammar is a TXL basis grammar and pretty printer for AT&T C++ V2.0.
        cp.Txl is a null transform that simply pretty prints the source
        as directed by the grammar.

        cpcount.Txl is a transform that always yields an empty result
        but has the side effect of printing statistics on use of declarations
        and statements in the input program.

        ANSIC.Grammar is a TXL basis grammar and pretty printer for ANSI C.
        c.Txl is a null transform that simply pretty prints the source
        as directed by the grammar.

        ccount.Txl is the same as cpcount.Txl but for ANSI C.

Author:
        J.R. Cordy

Affiliation:
        Queen's University, Kingston, Canada

Date:
        February 1992
        January 1994

Examples:
        txl groff.cp -comment           % pretty print groff.cp
        txl groff.cp cpcount.Txl        % count kinds of statements in groff.cp
        txl user.c -comment             % pretty print user.c
        txl user.c ccount.Txl           % count kinds of statements in user.c
